    "For example, relatively good (intra-daily) news reduces future or next-day volatility (Chen and Ghysels 2011).",
    "The prediction of Bitcoin's realized volatility depends on historical realized volatilities and jumps (Qiu et al. 2021).",
    "For instance, Patton and Sheppard (2015) argue that future volatility highly depends on the volatility of past negative returns and that the sign of the jump matters for the impact of price jumps on volatility, such as positive (negative) jumps lower (raise) future volatility."
